      <div class="modal-header">
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
        <h4 class="modal-title" id="gridSystemModalLabel2">CREAST &amp; MOTTO</h4>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body" >
<h3>The Mottos</h3>
<p>The original motto of the school was “ICH DIEN”. At the first Old Boys’ Dinner held in 1907, it was decided to use “NIHIL PER SALTUM” as a secondary motto. Prince of Wales’ College is the only school in Sri Lanka which has two mottos.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<h4>ICH DIEN</h4>
<p>A German phrase which translates to “I Serve”.</p></li>
<li>
<h4>NIHIL PER SALTUM</h4>
<p>A Latin phrase which translates to “Step-by-Step”</p></li>
</ul>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-danger" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
        
