      <div class="modal-body" >
   <div class="entry-content">
<p>This prestigious school was founded by Sir Henry Charles De Zoysa, one of the greatest ever philanthropists in Sri Lanka in 1876. Since then, Prince of Wales College produced many great personalities in various fields over the years during its proud history of 141 years. Past principals, teachers, and non-academic staff has done a great service in that regard.
Prince of Wales’ College has a very committed and talented academic and non-academic staff that always facilitates teaching-learning process in an effective and efficient manner with a view to develop the skills, knowledge and attitudes of students. While focusing on educational development, the college provides various co-curricular and extra curricular activities for students at the school. Special result enhancement programs are conducted for students facing Grade 05 Scholarship, G.C.E. Ordinary Level and G.C.E. Advanced level examinations on annual basis. Also motivational and attitude building programs are conducted for students in various grades. Prince of Wales College provides plenty of sports facilities for its students and over the years it has become as a famous school for sports. Also there is a good environment for students to develop their artistic talents at the College and it produced many artists who won national and international awards during last few decades. As well as all the students are guided to become effective professionals in their chosen fields and the college produced many great professionals in the history.Prince of Wales College has a strong and committed School Development Society and Old Boys Union that always assist for the school development. We all are working together to produce many more Cambrians who will make our motherland proud in the future..</p>
